.TH ADMIRALCTL-ADMIN 8 "June 2026" "Admiral" "Admiral Administration"
.SH NAME
admiralctl-admin \- administration workflows for the Admiral PaaS
.SH DESCRIPTION
This manual describes common administrative tasks and workflows using
.B admiralctl
to manage the Admiral control plane and worker nodes.
.SH WORKFLOWS
.SS Initial Setup
After installing the
.B admirald
control plane, initialize the CLI:
.IP
.B admiralctl init --server https://admiral.example.com --token $ADMIRAL_ADMIN_TOKEN
.IP
Verify the connection:
.IP
.B admiralctl status
.SS Scaling Infrastructure
To add a new worker node to the cluster:
.IP
1. Provision a Linux server with Podman installed.
.IP
2. Register the node in the control plane:
.IP
.B admiralctl nodes register --id worker-02 --hostname worker-02.local --ip 192.168.1.12 --role worker
.IP
3. Enable the node to start accepting workloads:
.IP
.B admiralctl nodes enable worker-02
.IP
4. Check node health:
.IP
.B admiralctl nodes ready --node worker-02
.SS Application Management
Registering a new application template:
.IP
.B admiralctl apps apply -f wordpress-template.yaml
.IP
Activate it for customers:
.IP
.B admiralctl apps activate --name wordpress
.SS Instance Lifecycle
Provisioning a new instance for a customer:
.IP
.B admiralctl instances provision --app wordpress --tier pro --customer cust-123 --wait
.IP
If a node needs maintenance, migrate the instance:
.IP
.B admiralctl instances migrate --target-node worker-03 inst-abc-123 --wait
.SS Disaster Recovery
Configure backup storage (S3 example):
.IP
.B admiralctl backups storage set --backend s3 --bucket admiral-backups --endpoint https://s3.example.com
.IP
.B admiralctl backups storage test
.IP
Trigger a manual backup:
.IP
.B admiralctl instances backup --service mysql inst-abc-123
.IP
Restore an instance from a backup:
.IP
.B admiralctl instances stop inst-abc-123
.IP
.B admiralctl backups restore --backup-id bkp-789 --instance-id inst-abc-123 --service mysql
.IP
.B admiralctl instances start inst-abc-123
.SS Auditing and Reporting
Check for instances exceeding storage limits:
.IP
.B admiralctl storage instances --output json | jq '.[] | select(.storage_exceeded == true)'
.IP
List recent platform operations:
.IP
.B admiralctl operations list
.SS Secret Key Rotation
Set the new encryption key in \fBsecrets_key\fR and retain the old key in
\fBsecrets_key_previous\fR in \fB/etc/admirald.ini\fR. Then run:
.IP
.B admiralctl secrets rotate
.IP
The command migrates stored ciphertexts through the admirald API and is
idempotent. It does not write directly to the PostgreSQL database. After
verification, remove the previous key and restart admirald according to the
sysadmin procedure.
.SS User Management
Create a new support operator:
.IP
.B admiralctl user create support-jane --type support
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR admiralctl (1),
.BR admirald (8)
